A programmer stores the total number of bytes in a small buffer and then subtracts one to get the last valid index. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <cstddef>
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    std::size_t buffer_size { 0 };
    std::size_t last_index { buffer_size - 1 };
    std::cout << last_index << "\n";
    return 0;
}
```
